<PageLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  eyebrow="Privacy Hub"
  heading="Privacy Policy"
  intro="Last updated April 2026. Plain-language version below; full legal text available on request."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1487058792275-0ad4aaf24ca7?w=1600&q=80&auto=format&fit=crop"
>
  <h2>What we collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Account info:</strong> name, email, age, photos you upload.</li>
    <li><strong>Profile info:</strong> bio, vibes, interests you choose to share.</li>
    <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> how you use the app, anonymized for product analytics.</li>
    <li><strong>Device data:</strong> device type, OS version, crash logs.</li>
    <li><strong>Location:</strong> only with your permission, only for matching nearby people.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What we don't do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>We don't sell your data. Ever.</li>
    <li>We don't share your contacts unless you ask us to.</li>
    <li>We don't read your messages — they're encrypted in transit and at rest.</li>
    <li>We don't run third-party ad trackers in the app.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>You can download, correct, or delete your data anytime from in-app settings. Under GDPR, CCPA, and similar laws, you have the right to access and erase your information. Email <a href="mailto:privacy@duncit.com">privacy@duncit.com</a> if you need help.</p>

  <h2>Retention</h2>
  <p>We keep account data while your account is active. After deletion, most data is removed within 30 days; some is kept for legal compliance (e.g., abuse reports) for up to 12 months.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>For privacy questions or to file a request: <a href="mailto:privacy@duncit.com">privacy@duncit.com</a>.</p>
</PageLayout>
